  "name": "Variable Buzzer Pitch",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Variable Buzzer Pitch",
    "description": "A pot in series cannot drive the buzzer — there is not enough current. Use an NMOS like lesson 71: USB → T → pot → 10kΩ → gate (corner at 5,8) varies Vgs as you turn the knob; the FET switches the loud path USB → T → 150Ω → buzzer → drain, source → ground. More resistance in the pot leg = lower gate voltage = quieter buzz. Compare lesson 14 (pot feeds an LED directly), lesson 71 (tact → NMOS), and lesson 73 (sensor → NMOS). Pot and buzzer at 90°; NMOS at 90°."
  },
